1. Start with 
$$Y_7 = \frac{A\,R_p}{B\,R_d + C\,R_p}\,. $$
Since $R_p\propto S_{34}$ and $R_d$, $A$, $B$, $C$ are independent of $S_{34}$, we have 
$$\frac{\partial\ln Y_7}{\partial\ln S_{34}}
=\frac{\partial\ln Y_7}{\partial\ln R_p}\,. $$

2. Write
$$\ln Y_7 = \ln A + \ln R_p - \ln\bigl(B R_d + C R_p\bigr)\,. $$
Differentiating with respect to $\ln R_p$ gives
$$\frac{\partial\ln Y_7}{\partial\ln R_p}
=1 - \frac{C R_p}{B R_d + C R_p}
=\frac{B R_d}{B R_d + C R_p}\,. $$

3. Given $C R_p = f\,B R_d$ with $f=\tfrac19$, substitute:
$$\frac{B R_d}{B R_d + C R_p}
=\frac{B R_d}{B R_d + f\,B R_d}
=\frac{1}{1+f}
=\frac{1}{1+\tfrac19}
=\frac{9}{10}\,. $$

Thus 
$$\frac{\partial\ln Y_7}{\partial\ln S_{34}}=\frac{9}{10}\,. $$

1. In quasi-static equilibrium (QSE), the abundance of $^7$Be satisfies
$$n_{^3\text{He}}\,n_{^4\text{He}}\langle\sigma v\rangle_{p}
 \;=\;n_{n}\,n_{^7\text{Be}}\,\langle\sigma v\rangle_{d}\,.$$
2. Since light-nuclei densities $n_{^3\text{He}},n_{^4\text{He}},n_n$ are unchanged to first order in $\epsilon$, 
$$N_{^7\text{Be}}\propto\frac{\langle\sigma v\rangle_{p}}{\langle\sigma v\rangle_{d}}
 \propto T_b^{\,\nu_p-\nu_d}\,.$$
3. The final $^7$Li/H tracks $N_{^7\text{Be}}$, so
$$\frac{N_{^7\text{Li}}/N_H}{(N_{^7\text{Li}}/N_H)_{\rm std}}
 =\Bigl(\frac{T_b}{T_\gamma}\Bigr)^{\nu_p-\nu_d}
 =(1+\epsilon)^{\nu_p-\nu_d}\,.$$
4. To first order in $\epsilon$, 
$$(1+\epsilon)^{\nu_p-\nu_d}-1\approx(\nu_p-\nu_d)\,\epsilon\,.$$
Thus the fractional change is $(\nu_p-\nu_d)\epsilon$.
